 ans:["I played football at club level for ten years and competed in running until my late twenties.","Three times a week is manageable. Saturdays are free. I want to commit fully or not at all.","Losing used to destroy me. I've learned to separate my self-worth from results — but I still hate it.","A great teammate shows up consistently, communicates honestly, and makes others around them better.","Fresh energy, discipline from outside the current dynamic, perspective not coloured by those losses.","Running my first marathon at 35 after a knee reconstruction — it taught me limitations are mostly mental."],
